Mobility - Walking

1 Description of DataSchema variable

The description of harmonised variable is the following:

  • Short name: mob_walk
  • Variable label: Mobility - walking
  • Variable description: Difficulty for walking by yourself and without using any special equipment
  • Domain: Health status and functional limitations
  • Value type: categorical
  • Category coding:
Code Category Label
0 Yes
1 No
  • Category missings:
Code Category Label
991 CAPI/interviewer error
992 Impute
993 Disable to measure
994 Not attempt/not done
995 Does not answer
996 Not applicable
997 Refuse
998 Do not know
999 Missing

2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute the harmonize variable from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • ((hefunc==-9))&(hemobwa==-9) into 997
  • (hefunc==-8)&(hemobwa==-8) into 998
  • ((hefunc==-1))&(hemobwa==-1) into 996
  • (hefunc==1) & (hemobwa!=1) into 1
  • ((hefunc==-9)|(hefunc==-8))&(hemobwa==0) into 1
  • Otherwise<-0

R script:

ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1_mob_walk$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w1_mob_walk$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk[((ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hefunc == 1) & (ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hemobwa != 
    1))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk[(((ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hefunc == -9) | (ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hefunc == 
    -8)) & (ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hemobwa == 0))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk[(((ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hefunc == -1)) & (ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hemobwa == 
    -1))] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk[((ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hefunc == -9) & (ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hemobwa == 
    -9))] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk[((ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hefunc == -8) & (ELSA_w1_mob_walk$hemobwa == 
    -8))] <- 998

ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk <- labelled(ELSA_ds_w1$mob_walk, labels = c(Yes = 0, No = 1, 
    Not_applicable = 996, Refuse = 997, Do_not_know = 998))
